entries.title: Shipments of Armored Vehicles Reflect West's Growing Confidence in Ukrainian Arms
entries.description: Now is seen as the ‘right time’ for Kyiv to change course of the war, but also to prepare for a Russian counteroffensive.

entries.title: U.S. Sails Warship Through Taiwan Strait as China Watches Sternly
entries.description: The first such transit this year follows nine in 2022, activities that Beijing protests.

entries.title: Mexico Boosts Military Presence After Son of 'El Chapo' Is Captured
entries.description: At least 29 people died in the military operation to capture Ovidio Guzmán on Thursday, including 10 soldiers, authorities said.

entries.title: State Department Recognizes Türkiye as Turkey's Formal Name
entries.description: Ankara had requested nations use the Turkish language name rather than anglicized spelling and pronunciation.

entries.title: Ukraine Clashes Continue Despite Russia's Cease-Fire Calls
entries.description: Russian President Vladimir Putin had proposed a 36-hour truce to mark Russian Orthodox Christmas, but Kyiv dismissed it as a ploy.

entries.title: How a Billion Lost Eggs Show the Challenges Facing Ukraine's Economy
entries.description: Avangard Group’s Chornobaivske chicken farm used to export a billion eggs a year, but its dilapidated condition tells of the likely lasting impact of the war on Ukraine’s economy.

entries.title: China to Allow Rapid Tests to Confirm Covid Cases
entries.description: Beijing is dismantling the remaining vestiges of the zero-Covid regime that governed the country for the past three years.

entries.title: Sliding Natural-Gas Prices Deal Surprise Reprieve to Europe
entries.description: Prices have halved over a month, easing worries of an industrial meltdown, but the benefits will take months to fully feed through to most businesses and consumers.

entries.title: China-Developed mRNA Covid Vaccine Starts Test Production
entries.description: Chinese drugmaker CanSino Biologics started trial production of a vaccine using mRNA Technology to target new variants of Covid-19 that are behind the country’s current outbreak.

entries.title: Warmer Weather Helps Ease Europe's War-Driven Inflation Surge
entries.description: While consumer prices fell more than expected in December, the European Central Bank has signaled it has more to do to tame inflation.
